FeedPackage.Description:
A library to help create small application modules that are dependency and test friendly. It is the base for modules as micro-services. There are two concepts: The chains and the actions. The chains act like a state machine representation of the class, holding a context, which actions can be applied. While actions are applied either the data or context returned might change. Using common patterns over this methodology small components can be build that can be easily testable and injectable through each other.
Supports Mono.

Using common patterns over this methodology small components can be build that can be easily testable and injectable through each other.
(Check the examples at the project link)
Supports Mono.
